-- Tier 3 (NO-SHORTCUT, ODSE-ONLY) — land dbo.LAB101 (was 0/46)
-- Agent R6t6-lab101. UID block 22074000-22074999 (catalog/uid_ranges.md).
-- =====================================================================
-- Branch aw/remove-nrt-shortcut: authors ONLY NBS_ODSE rows (act /
-- observation / obs_value_* / act_relationship / act_id / participation).
-- CDC -> nrt_observation; service sp_observation_event + ProcessObservation
-- DataUtil; orchestrator Step-5 sp_d_lab_test_postprocessing +
-- sp_d_labtest_result_postprocessing; Step-9 sp_lab101_datamart_post-
-- processing turn these into LAB101 rows. NO nrt_* INSERT, NO EXEC sp_,
-- NO liquibase/seed/SRTE/routine edits.
--
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ROOT CAUSE — WHY LAB101 STAYED 0/46 AFTER zz_lab100_101_fill.sql
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
-- VERIFIED LIVE (RDB_MODERN, 2026-06-04):
--   * The prior fixture's full I_Order/I_Result/Result + 35 LABxxx chain
--     IS present in LAB_TEST (37 I_Result rows, ROOT_ORDERED_TEST_PNTR =
--     22053500), and LAB_RESULT_VAL / TEST_RESULT_GROUPING / LAB_TEST_
--     RESULT all landed (37 / 37 / 38 rows). Yet LAB101 = 0.
--   * sp_lab101_datamart_postprocessing (020) STEP 2 (#tmp_I_Result_vals,
--     lines 51-70) reads dbo.nrt_observation.followup_observation_uid of
--     the I_Result's ROOT_ORDERED_TEST_PNTR observation and filters it to
--     LAB_TEST_TYPE='I_Result'. Every I_Result row's ROOT_ORDERED_TEST_PNTR
--     is 22053500, whose obs_domain_cd_st_1 = 'I_Order'.
--   * nrt_observation(22053500).followup_observation_uid IS NULL (verified;
--     ALL 22053xxx rows have NULL followup), so STEP 2 returns 0 rows and
--     the whole LAB101 chain starves -> 0/46.
--
-- WHY THE FOLLOWUP CSV IS NULL (the actual gate — bug #16):
--   followup_observation_uid is written by the reporting-pipeline-service
--   (ProcessObservationDataUtil.transformFollowupObservations), NOT by the
--   routines. That method, at its first line inside the per-child loop, runs
--       assertDomainCdMatches(obsDomainCdSt1, ORDER);     // ORDER = "Order"
--   (ProcessObservationDataUtil.java:310, assert at :573-577). When the ROOT
--   observation's obs_domain_cd_st_1 != exactly 'Order' it THROWS
--   IllegalArgumentException, the catch (:327) swallows it, and
--   setFollowUpObservationUid is NEVER called. The prior fixture's root was
--   obs_domain_cd_st_1='I_Order', so its followup CSV could never populate.
--   (This is the empty bugs/16_followup_observations_npe_null_domain stub:
--    an 'I_Order'/'R_Order' root can NEVER get a followup CSV through the
--    real pipeline. Only an 'Order'-domain root does — proven by the working
--    CDC CELR lab 20070010 (domain 'Order') whose followup = '20070020,
--    20070021', and by bug #3's morb fix walking a 'C_Result' followup off
--    an 'Order' root.)
--
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE FIX — author an 'Order'-DOMAIN root above the I_Order
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
-- The service sets report_observation_uid for EVERY observation whose COMP
-- parent's domain CONTAINS "Order" (ProcessObservationDataUtil:352,
-- parentDomainCd.contains(ORDER) — true for 'Order','I_Order','C_Order').
-- The followup walk in sp_observation_event (055, lines 132-153) is a 4-level
-- source->target descendant union off the root, so an 'Order' root reaches
-- I_Result GRANDCHILDREN. So we author a 3-tier ODSE hierarchy:
--
--   Order root 22074500  (obs_domain_cd_st_1='Order')   <-- followup-bearing
--        ^ COMP
--   I_Order    22074501  (obs_domain_cd_st_1='I_Order')
--        ^ COMP
--   Result     22074502  (obs_domain_cd_st_1='Result')  + 35 I_Result
--   I_Result   22074600..22074634 (cd LAB329a,LAB330..LAB363)
--
-- RESOLUTION (verified against routines 018 / 020 + service):
--   * Order root 22074500 is domain 'Order' -> assert passes -> service
--     writes its followup_observation_uid = the 4-level descendant CSV,
--     which INCLUDES the 35 I_Result grandchildren + the Result + I_Order.
--   * Each I_Result child's COMP parent is the I_Order (domain 'I_Order'
--     contains "Order") -> report_observation_uid = 22074501 ->
--     LAB_TEST.PARENT_TEST_PNTR = 22074501 (an 'I_Order' row), satisfying
--     sp_lab101 step 3's "...where lab_test_type='I_Order'" join (020:179).
--   * The I_Order's COMP parent is the Order root (domain 'Order') ->
--     I_Order.report_observation_uid = 22074500. For an I_Result,
--     sp_d_lab_test_postprocessing (018:406) computes ROOT_ORDERED_TEST_PNTR
--     = parent_test(=I_Order 22074501).report_observation_uid = 22074500.
--     So every I_Result's ROOT_ORDERED_TEST_PNTR = the 'Order' root, whose
--     followup CSV IS populated -> sp_lab101 step 2 #tmp_I_Result_vals
--     resolves -> step 3 (#tmp_ISOLATE_TRACKING_INIT, from LAB_RESULT_VAL of
--     those I_Result uids) drives the 35-col trtdN pivot -> LAB101 lands.
--   * The 35 obs_value_coded.display_name -> TEST_RESULT_VAL_CD_DESC (017
--     :731-733) feed LAB1..LAB35; the 7 datetime pivot cds (LAB334/349/350/
--     356/357/361/362) carry obs_value_date.from_time -> FROM_TIME so the
--     hard convert(datetime) in 020:839-845 only ever sees a datetime or
--     NULL and cannot throw.
--
-- DISTINCT FROM THE PRIOR FIXTURE: this lands LAB101 because the followup-
-- bearing root is a true 'Order' (not 'I_Order'). It reuses NO 22053xxx UID
-- and edits nothing; it is an independent, idempotent NOT-EXISTS-guarded add
-- in block 22074xxx. (The dormant 22053xxx I_Order-rooted chain is harmless:
-- its followup stays NULL by design and contributes 0 LAB101 rows.)
--
